This paper proposes a novel constituency parsing scheme using neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques, such as neural networks, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction, which is a common technique in computer vision, falling under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
